        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 11:49PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1146 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over much of Crockett County from southern Crockett
County on north to along I-10 around Ozona to Sheffield, moving
northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
The Intersection Of Us 190 And Highway 163, The Intersection Of Ranch
Road 2083 And Highway 405, The Intersection Of Highway 163 And Ranch
Road 1973, Ozona, I-10 Near The Crockett-Pecos County Line, Us-
190 Near The Crockett-
Sutton County Line, Ft Lancaster, The Intersection Of I-
10 And Highway 405, The Intersection Of I-10 And Highway 290, and I-
10 Near The Crockett-Sutton County Line.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 327 and 380.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
